======================================================================
RESTRICTION MAP DIMENSION ANALYSIS
======================================================================

For β₁(T)=0 tournaments: Z¹(T) has dim = n-1 = dim(B¹(T)).
For β₁(T\v)=1: Z¹(T\v) has dim = n-1, B¹(T\v) has dim = n-2.
Question: what is rank(res_v|_{Z¹(T)})?

n=5 restriction map ranks (all β₁=0 tournaments with bad vertices):
  Rank distribution of res_v|_Z¹(T) (over all bad (T,v) pairs):
    rank=3: 840 cases

  Image properties (all bad pairs):
    Total bad (T,v) pairs: 840
    Image ⊂ Z¹(T\v): 840/840
    Image ⊂ B¹(T\v): 840/840
    (If image ⊂ B¹ always, then res_v kills H¹ => non-trivial cocycle is NOT extendable)


======================================================================
KEY STRUCTURAL TEST
======================================================================
When β₁(T)=0: does res_v: Z¹(T) → Z¹(T\v) always have image ⊂ B¹(T\v)?
This would mean: every cocycle on T restricts to a COBOUNDARY on T\v.
Contrapositive: if some cocycle restricts to non-coboundary, β₁(T) > 0.

  n=5: CONFIRMED — res_v(Z¹(T)) ⊂ B¹(T\v) for all v, all β₁=0 tournaments
  n=6: CONFIRMED — res_v(Z¹(T)) ⊂ B¹(T\v) for all v (27968 tournaments)


======================================================================
EXTENSION ANALYSIS
======================================================================
For each bad vertex v in a β₁=0 tournament:
  The non-trivial cocycle w_v of T\v — is it extendable to T?
  (Should NOT be, since β₁(T)=0.)

  n=5 (all bad (T,v) pairs):
    Extendable: 0
    Non-extendable: 840
    All non-trivial cocycles on T\v are non-extendable when β₁(T)=0.


======================================================================
COCYCLE / COBOUNDARY DIMENSIONS
======================================================================
For β₁(T)=0: dim Z¹(T) = dim B¹(T) = n-1.
For each vertex v:
  dim Z¹(T\v) = ? and dim B¹(T\v) = n-2.
  β₁(T\v) = dim Z¹(T\v) - (n-2)


n=5:
  dim Z¹(T\v) distribution (over all β₁(T)=0 tournaments, all v):
    dim=3 (β₁=0): 2760 cases
    dim=4 (β₁=1): 840 cases

n=6:
  dim Z¹(T\v) distribution (over all β₁(T)=0 tournaments, all v):
    dim=4 (β₁=0): 132480 cases
    dim=5 (β₁=1): 35328 cases


